The paper deals with graph drawings and network construction, which are topics commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of a self-approaching graph drawing is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.NA). Finally, the paper also discusses algorithms and computational complexity, which are relevant to computer science and information theory (cs.SI).
